        "tweet_summary": "Not every engineer will become a Product Engineer. AI is taking over more of the implementation...",
        "tweet_url": "https://x.com/SergioRocks/status/2041206854177394766",
        "draft": "El ingeniero que pregunta \"por qué estamos construyendo esto\" antes de escribir una línea vale tres que ya tienen el PR listo. AI hizo que la ejecución sea commodity. La decisión de qué ejecutar nunca lo fue."
      },
      {
        "id": "r2",
        "to": "@SergioRocks",
        "tweet_summary": "AI is a force multiplier for bad processes. AI doesn't fix your thinking. It executes it.",
        "tweet_url": "https://x.com/SergioRocks/status/2040119691750826409",
        "draft": "This is why \"just add AI\" fails. I've seen companies automate a broken onboarding flow and get 10x the complaints in half the time. The first question isn't \"can AI do this?\" — it's \"should this process exist at all?\""
